My name is Arash Zakeresfahani.

I am a third year Ph.D. student at Indiana University. I study Health Informatics and Human-Computer Interaction. I use a variety of quantitative and qualitative research methods to study communities of pregnancy care providers and identify healthcare resources in Indiana. My goal is to use human-center and participatory design to develop interactive technologies to improve access to pregnancy-related resourcess in marginalized and rural communities. The most enjoyable part of my work is interacting with my study participants and learning about their experiences.
